text: <!channel> Hey dev team just wanted to give you a head’s up - rather than have you join tomorrow’s creative touch base as planned, we’re going to forego that and set up a regular meeting between dev and ux to review wireframes

this is likely going to come a bit later than expected based on changes coming out of the ProChange meetings that have gone on the past two days, but will be awesome to get a dedicated time where you can all ask questions, provide feedback, etc
Is there any way to get the material from the meeting tomorrow? It would be beneficial to be able to discuss it while all the devs are here this week.
Do you mean in regards to UX specifically? Or generally speaking?

I ask because we’re no longer planning to show any UX tomorrow, as things are currently changing pretty significantly. The changes won’t dictate a fundamental shift in how we’re approaching things right now, but there won’t be even draft wires ready yet that take into account these ProChange shifts
Instead we’ll focus on design, which again will be informed by the UX work that is in flux. So we can share out some design progress if that’s helpful, but it won’t map back to any wires.
you’re right that that doesn’t sound *as helpful* but everything we can get our eyes on will help!
I definitely hear ya - let me see what we can get together to share to dev after tomorrow’s meeting from the visual side. I’ll keep you posted!
I just drove 10 hours and my up thinks thinks I took 7800 steps
you should put that in the up-insights channel on compass slack!
